# AHS to AFS bias leads to re-assignment to FR as soon as it is not congested

network
 handover2 assignment 1
 handover2 afs-bias rxqual 1
 handover2 min-free-slots tch/f 2

create-bts trx-count 1 timeslots c+s4 TCH/F TCH/F TCH/F TCH/H  TCH/H TCH/H PDCH
set-ts-use trx 0 0 states        *    TCH/F -     -     TCH/H- -     -     *

meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 0 ta 0
expect-no-chan

# congestion on TCH/F goes away
set-ts-use trx 0 0 states        *    -     -     -     TCH/H- -     -     *

# this time move a TCH/H to TCH/F because of AHS to AFS bias
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
meas-rep lchan 0 0 4 0 rxlev 40 rxqual 1 ta 0
#expect-ho from lchan 0 0 4 0 to lchan 0 0 1 0
expect-ts-use trx 0 0 states     *    TCH/F -     -     -      -     -     *

